  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Purpose</strong><br>\nThe Finance Executive is responsible for handling the finance related matter which includes accounts payable, accounts receivable and purchasing functions of the school.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Main Duties</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in verification of supplier invoices to ensure they are correct and valid and obtain relevant parties’ signatures for payment approvals.</li>\n  <li>Perform data entry into accounting systems.</li>\n  <li>Manage students’ billings.</li>\n  <li>Manage procurement for school purchases.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and maintain uniform stock and sales reconciliation monthly.</li>\n  <li>Process refunds for students, if any.</li>\n  <li>Compile and check staff reimbursements.</li>\n  <li>Provide support in school’s daily finance operations.</li>\n  <li>Other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for the purchasing functions of the School.</li>\n  <li>Act as a back-up and cover the Front Desk duties as and when required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least a Diploma in Accounting or equivalent</li>\n  <li>At least 3 – 5 years’ work experience</li>\n  <li>Good knowledge of Microsoft Excel and SAGE preferred</li>\n  <li>Attention to detail and accuracy</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal skills especially in dealing with parents and students</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
